  "name": "2 Kings 11:1-16:20",
  "localizedName": "2 Kings 11:1-16:20",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108490",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Athaliah"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " was from Ahab’s family but hadn’t been killed by Jehu. She ruled over the southern kingdom until "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108491",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Joash"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " was seven years old."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Joash’s aunt Jehosheba and his uncle "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108492",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Jehoiada"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " had kept Joash safe from Athaliah. Jehoiada taught Joash the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108335",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Law of Moses"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". Jehoiada led the king and the people to commit themselves again to the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108328",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Mount Sinai covenant"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "In the northern kingdom, kings continued to be compared to Jeroboam. The rest of Israel’s kings committed Jeroboam’s sins of worshipping "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108284",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "false gods"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". This included Jehoahaz, Jehoash, Jeroboam the second and Zechariah. Zechariah was the last king in Jehu’s family line."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "When Jehoash was king, Aram’s kings Hazael and Ben-Hadad treated the Israelites very badly. Elisha had prophesied about this. Even though Jehoash wasn’t faithful to God, God had "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108342",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "mercy"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " on the Israelites. Elisha had Jehoash shoot arrows. These were a sign of how God would save the Israelites. Jehoash was very sad when Elisha died."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Later, the kings Shallum, Menahem, Pekahiah, Pekah and Hoshea ruled in the northern kingdom. They all did evil and worshipped false gods. In the southern kingdom, the kings Joash, Amaziah, Uzziah and Jotham were faithful to God’s "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108237",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "covenant"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". But none of Judah’s kings followed God with all their "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108419",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "heart"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " like "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108449",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "David"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " had done."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "When Ahaz was king of Judah he didn’t follow God at all. He followed the examples of the northern kingdom and of the people groups around them. Ahaz didn’t trust God to protect the southern kingdom. Instead, he trusted the king of "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108493",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "Assyria"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". This led Ahaz to make changes to how people worshipped God in the "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108417",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "temple"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": ". He made these changes to honour Assyria's king and false gods."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
